  "title": "Project Engineer (Security Systems)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>•\tManage and coordinate service-related projects from start to completion</p><p>•\tPlan, design, configure, and commission security system setups</p><p>•\tRead and interpret technical drawings and specifications</p><p>•\tSupport service and maintenance activities, including project-to-maintenance transition</p><p>•\tProvide technical guidance and on-site support to service technicians when required</p><p>•\tParticipate in material selection, technical submissions, and purchase requests</p><p>•\tMonitor project progress, schedule, stock status, and cost control</p><p>•\tCoordinate with customers, vendors, and other contractors</p><p>•\tSupervise installation teams and ensure quality and safety compliance</p><p>•\tPrepare regular progress updates and reports to the Project Manager</p><p><br /><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><p>•\tDiploma or Degree in Electrical, Electronics, IT, or related field</p><p>•\tExperience in security systems service and project execution</p><p>•\tStrong technical and system commissioning skills</p><p>•\tGood coordination, communication, and problem-solving abilities</p><p>•\tPossess driving license will be advantageous</p><p>•\tAbility to perform documentation work on Microsoft applications etc.</p>",
